1 AN ACT concerning school districts elections; relating to question
2 submitted elections on the issuance of bonds by a school district;
3 validating the election results for the bond issuance question submitted
4 by the board of education of USD 200, Greeley county; relating to
5 election publication requirements; providing for publication on the
6 website of the county election office if such office has a website;
7 amending K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 10-120 and repealing the existing
8 section.
9
10 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
11 New Section 1. The result of the election held on May 21, 2024, on
12 the question submitted by the board of education of unified school district
13 no. 200, Greeley county, for the purpose of authorizing the issuance of
14 general obligation bonds in an amount not to exceed $4,600,000 to pay the
15 costs to: (a) Construct, furnish, equip and acquire improvements, additions
16 and renovations to the school district's elementary and junior/senior high
17 school facility, including safety and security improvements, playground
18 improvements, locker room additions and renovations, a gymnasium
19 addition and improvements to comply with the Americans with disabilities
20 act; (b) construct, furnish, equip and acquire other necessary renovations
21 and improvements to school district facilities; (c) make all other necessary
22 improvements appurtenant thereto; and (d) pay the costs of issuance and
23 interest on the bonds during construction of the project is hereby declared
24 valid, and the board of education may issue such general obligation bonds
25 as otherwise provided by law in an amount not to exceed $4,600,000 for
26 the purposes specified herein.
27 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 10-120 is hereby amended to read as
28 follows: 10-120. (a) Whenever an election is required for the issuance of
29 bonds for any purpose by any municipality other than an irrigation
30 district or where a different procedure for giving notice of the election is
31 specifically provided by law, upon compliance with the legal
32 requirements necessary and precedent to the call for the election, the
33 proper municipal officers shall call an election. The election shall be
34 held within 60 days after compliance with the necessary requirements,
35 or within 90 days, should the longer period include the date of a general
36 election.

