1 (b) Notice of the election shall be published in a newspaper of
2 general circulation in the municipality once each week for two
3 consecutive weeks and on the website of the county election office of any
4 county where the election is to be conducted if such county election office
5 has a website. The first publication shall be not less than 21 days prior to
6 the election. Notice of the election shall also be published on the website
7 of the county election office of any county where the election is to be
8 conducted. Such notice shall be published not less than 21 days prior to the
9 election and If published on the website of the county election office, such
10 publication shall remain on the website until the day after the election.
11 The notice shall set forth the time and place of holding the election and
12 the purpose for which the bonds are to be issued and shall be signed by
13 the county election officer. The election shall be held at the usual place
14 of holding elections and shall be conducted by the officers or persons
15 provided by law for holding elections in the municipality.
16 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 10-120 is hereby repealed.
17 Sec. 2. 4. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
18 publication in the Kansas register.

